04/02/2005
WASHINGTON, United States â US Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld met with visiting Albanian counterpart Pandeli Majko on Wednesday (2 February).
They agreed bilateral relations in the sphere of defence are excellent.
While Rumsfeld expressed gratitude for Albania's contribution to the operations in Iraq, Majko thanked the US administration for supporting Albania's NATO aspirations.
In other news, the major Albanian political parties met again on Thursday but failed to reach any breakthrough on electoral reform.
The talks, mediated by the OSCE, focused on the new distribution of electoral zones.
(Albanian Daily News, ATA - 04/02/05)
